summary: This is a search warrant issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York authorizing the search of a large multi-story residence in New York, NY. The warrant is related to violations of sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy, and it details the premises to be searched and the items to be seized, including evidence of occupancy and the layout of the property.

persons.name: Barbara Moses
persons.context: Issued and signed the search warrant for the Subject Premises in New York, NY.

events.title: Search Warrant Issued for New York Residence
events.description: A federal search warrant was issued authorizing the search of a nearly 19,000 square foot multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY, for evidence related to sex trafficking of minors and conspiracy.

locations: Subject Premises: a nearly 19,000 square foot multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY
keyFacts: The search warrant targets a nearly 19,000 square foot multi-story single-family residence in New York, NY.
The warrant is related to violations of Title 18, U.S. Code, Sections 371 (conspiracy) and 1591 (sex trafficking of minors).
Items authorized for seizure include evidence of occupancy/ownership (bills, mail, IDs, photos) and evidence of the property's layout (photos, blueprints).
The warrant was issued by U.S. Magistrate Judge Barbara Moses on or about August 2, 2017.
The warrant authorizes photographing and video recording the full interior of the premises.
